western\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new structure \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 which will house the Wildcats through the 2025 season \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 finally has a name.\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\", \"score\": 0.9378261830652886, \"rank\": 0.06568731511621785, \"text\": \"Wildcats\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Monday, the school announced that it reached a two-year naming-rights partnership with Northwestern Medicine.\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1303, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.966032846583006e-14, \"text\": \"Northwestern Medicine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The temporary stadium will be named Northwestern Medicine Field at Martin Stadium for the next two football seasons.\", \"from\": 1326, \"to\": 1442, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are honored to expand our partnership with Northwestern Medicine, as they continue to invest in our University, including Northwestern Athletics,\\\" saidNorthwestern University president Michael Schill.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1512, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.966032846583006e-14, \"text\": \"Northwestern Medicine\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Feinberg_School_of_Medicine\"}, {\"begin\": 1570, \"end\": 1582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\", \"score\": 0.9360983697153044, \"rank\": 0.06740136221074886, \"text\": \"Northwestern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This partnership will help bring our innovative venue on the lakefront to life and bring our community together.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would also like to thank the Martin Family for their continued support of Northwestern Athletics and the University.\\\"\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\", \"score\": 0.9360983697153044, \"rank\": 0.06740136221074886, \"text\": \"Northwestern\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Wildcats_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t get enough of the view from Northwestern Medicine Field at Martin Stadium \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u008d#B1GFootballx@NUFBFamilypic.twitter.com/xwfyYBqBCf  It took Northwestern some time to find a solution for home football games for the next two seasons.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The school has demolished Ryan Field and is constructing a brand new, state-of-the-art stadium to call home.\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2148, \"end\": 2158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hemet-Ryan_Airport\", \"score\": 0.999997066789756, \"rank\": 1.6849500782259648e-06, \"text\": \"Ryan Field\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hemet-Ryan_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hemet-Ryan_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, Northwestern decided to build a temporary structure so it could still play a majority of its home football games in Evanston.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2360, \"end\": 2368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NorthShore_University_HealthSystem\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6786846827389271e-31, \"text\": \"Evanston\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NorthShore_University_HealthSystem\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NorthShore_University_HealthSystem\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Wildcats did schedule two games at Wrigley Field, playing Ohio State (Nov. 16) and Illinois (Nov. 30) at the Friendly Confines.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2374, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\", \"score\": 0.9378261830652886, \"rank\": 0.06568731511621785, \"text\": \"Wildcats\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\"}, {\"begin\": 2432, \"end\": 2442, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_State_Buckeyes_football\", \"score\": 0.9902925622259827, \"rank\": 0.009802307299260913, \"text\": \"Ohio State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_State_Buckeyes_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ohio_State_Buckeyes_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As the health care provider for the University's students and athletes, we are pleased to strengthen our partnership and continue supporting the Wildcats in this new venue,\\\" said Howard Chrisman, MD, president and chief executive officer, Northwestern Memorial HealthCare.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2649, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Wildcats\", \"s